    {
        "name": "FancyText Unicode",
        "category": "FancyText Unicode",
        "civilopediaText": [
            {  "text": "UTF-8 Symbols", "header": 1, },
            {  "text": "Using symbols in unit or city names adds flavor! All capitol cities and city-states in this mod have a symbol prefix. See jsons/English.properties", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "
Aliased cities look like:
Babylon = ⭐Babylon
Athens = ⭐Athens
Beijing = ⭐Beijing
...
Brussels = ⟰Brussels
Bucharest = ⟰Bucharest
Florence = ⟰Florence
...
", "padding": 5,},
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "header": 1, "text": "Why?", },
            {  "text": "The original purpose of this mod is to visualize which Unicode characters render in Unciv.", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "This works great for sorting, ID'ing at-a-glance, and other nuances. For example, spy_screen cities auto-sort, city_screen city names reveal CS or capitals, unit_screen can auto-sort special cities, etc.", },
            {  "text": "Also found by adding prefix symbol badges to high ranking units, this helps manage unit strategy faster. Different unit types or groups can be assigned their own ranks (manually of course, just another way to crawl).", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "Add prefixes to units like these examples:
⚛GDR Boss
⚍Lt Cmdr
⛉⛉⛉Sky Admiral (3rd rank)
⚑⭐Washington (flag says this is my capital city)", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "Within Unciv", "header": 5, },
            {  "text": "There does not appear to be a way to highlight-select text other than city or unit renaming. You can't copy any characters from here! :P 😝 😛 <-- and emoji smiley characters don't work fyi :P:P:P", },
            {  "text": "To use these characters, tap the link under the preview block within the section, copy the symbol from your browser, paste into an Unciv textbox in-game.", },
        ]
    },
